  "assumptions": "• The only relevant pieces of information are the lengths along the intersecting chords and the fact that ∠AEC = 90°. In our interpretation we set chord AB with AE = 8 and BE = 2 and chord CD with CE = 8 and ED = 2 (so that CE + ED = 10) and require that the rays EA and EC be perpendicular. This naturally sets up a coordinate system with E = (0,0), A = (8,0) and B = (–2,0) along the horizontal line, and C = (0,8) and D = (0,–2) along the vertical line. The circle ω is the unique circle through A, B, C, D. Its center is found from the perpendicular bisectors of AB and CD. Finally, a rectangle R is drawn inside ω whose sides are parallel to AB (horizontal) and CD (vertical) and (because its interior may not contain points on either chord or on the circle) R must lie entirely in one of the four open “quadrants” determined by the lines x = 0 and y = 0. In our coordinate choice the natural candidate is the first quadrant (x > 0, y > 0).",
